Projects
Ticket Sale Suggestion - A Case Study Using Association Rules
Summer 2020
Project URL: https://notlongp.github.io/ticket-association/
The goal of this case study is to understand what events are closely correlated based on each event's transactions. In order to achieve this
goal, this report makes use of association rules modeling, namely Apriori algorithm and Eclat algorithm.
Geostatistics Visualization Interface
Summer 2020
Project URL: https://github.com/notlongp/geostats-visual
A dynamic visualization tool for Geo-statistical analysis (exploratory data analysis such as correlation plots, boxplots, histograms, etc.

Predicting the Trajectory of Atlantic Hurricanes with a Statistical Model
Fall 2019
Project URL: https://notlongp.github.io/hurricane/
Trained the training data in Python using three statistical models, namely multiple regression, decision tree regression, and
XGBOOST, to accurately assess the trajectory in hurricanes once a storm system has been created using historical hurricane data
provided by the National Hurricane Center.
Using Twitter Data to Predict Stock Market Trends
Spring 2019
Project URL: https://notlongp.github.io/twitter-stock-correlation/
Assess the correlation between recorded tweets sentiment (scraped and processed using Python's "tweepy" and "nltk" packages) and the
changes within the stock market using the Gaussian Nave Bayes Classifier and an artificial neural network.
